title: fanoutqa: Who were the directors of movies that grossed over $700 million in 2023, and when did they direct their first movie? (Sort the directors from the one who directed their first movie earliest to the most recent.) (870881b3ef7e2866)

chat_history.content: Who were the directors of movies that grossed over $700 million in 2023, and when did they direct their first movie? (Sort the directors from the one who directed their first movie earliest to the most recent.)

Here is a list of directors whose films grossed over $700 million worldwide in 2023, sorted by their directorial debut date (oldest to most recent):

1. James Mangold: *Heavy* (1995) - *The Wolverine* (2013), *Logan* (2017), and *Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny* (2023) grossed $414.8 million, $619 million, and $757.2 million respectively.

2. James Cameron: *Piranha II: The Spawning* (1981) - *Avatar: The Way of Water* (2022) grossed $2.131 billion in 2022 and 2023 combined.

3. J. J. Abrams: *Regarding Henry* (1991) - *Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker* (2019) grossed $1.074 billion.

4. Jon Watts: *Clown* (2014) - *Spider-Man: No Way Home* (2021) grossed $1.921 billion.

5. Joseph Kosinski: *TRON: Legacy* (2010) - *Top Gun: Maverick* (2022) grossed $1.488 billion.

Please note that I have only included films released in 2023 or the previous few years, as these are the most relevant to the current context. Some directors may have had earlier films that met the criteria in previous years.
